            <mj-column padding-bottom="50px">
                <mj-image src="assets/images/iso-iec-27001-2022.png" alt="ISO 27001 UKAS Accredited Badge" title="ISO/IEC 27001:2022" />
                <mj-text mj-class="heading">Celebrating our ISO 27001 Accreditation</mj-text>
                <mj-text mj-class="paddit">We are thrilled to announce that Rapid has successfully achieved the prestigious <a href="https://rapid-is.co.uk/assets/files/british-assessment-bureau-certificate-23022024.pdf" target="_blank" title="ISO 27001">ISO 27001</a> accreditation! This significant milestone underscores our commitment to information security.</mj-text>
                <mj-text mj-class="subheading">What is ISO 27001?</mj-text>
                <mj-text mj-class="paddit">ISO 27001 is an internationally recognised standard that sets out the requirements for establishing, implementing, maintaining, and continually improving an Information Security Management System (ISMS). It provides a systematic approach to managing sensitive company information, ensuring its confidentiality, integrity, and availability.</mj-text>
                <mj-text mj-class="subheading">Our Journey to Accreditation</mj-text>
                <mj-text mj-class="paddit">The journey toward ISO 27001 accreditation was rigorous and collaborative. Here are some key highlights:</mj-text>
                <mj-text color="#525252" font-size="18px" font-weight="400" line-height="1.5">
                    <ol>
                        <li><strong>Risk Assessment and Gap Analysis:</strong> We conducted a thorough risk assessment and identified areas where improvements were needed to align with ISO 27001 requirements.</li>
                        <li><strong>Policy Development:</strong> Our dedicated team worked on developing robust information security policies and procedures. These policies cover everything from access controls to incident response.</li>
                        <li><strong>Employee Training and Awareness:</strong> We invested in training our employees to raise awareness about information security best practices. Everyone at Rapid played a crucial role in achieving this accreditation.</li>
                        <li><strong>Implementation and Controls:</strong> We implemented a range of technical and organisational controls to safeguard our information assets. Regular audits and reviews ensured compliance with ISO 27001 standards.</li>
                        <li><strong>Certification Audit:</strong> After months of preparation, we underwent a comprehensive certification audit conducted by an independent certification body. The audit evaluated our security protocols and risks measures against ISO 27001 requirements.</li>
                    </ol>
                </mj-text>
                <mj-text mj-class="subheading">What Does This Mean for Our Customers?</mj-text>
                <mj-text color="#525252" font-size="18px" font-weight="400" line-height="1.5">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Enhanced Security:</strong> Our ISO 27001 accreditation demonstrates our commitment to protecting our customers’ sensitive data. You can trust that your information is in safe hands.</li>
                        <li><strong>Continuous Improvement:</strong> Achieving ISO 27001 is not the end; it’s the beginning of a continuous improvement journey. We will regularly review and enhance our security practices to stay ahead of emerging threats.</li>
                        <li><strong>Peace of Mind:</strong> As our customer, you can rest assured that we follow industry best practices to keep your data secure. ISO 27001 provides peace of mind for both us and our clients.</li>
                    </ul>
                </mj-text>
                <mj-text mj-class="paddit">We extend our heartfelt gratitude to everyone who contributed to this achievement. Our team’s dedication, collaboration, and unwavering focus on security made this possible.</mj-text>
